This paper discusses security mechanisms and vulnerabilities in Firefox OS, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of static analysis to detect vulnerabilities, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL). The discussion of challenges in repurposing desktop software for a mobile operating system suggests a focus on systems (cs.SY) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
